'''Leo Skiri Østigård''' (born 28 November 1999) is a Norwegian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{Italian football updater|Genoa}} club [[Genoa CFC|Genoa]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]].<ref name=soccerway>{{Soccerway|leo-skiri-oestigaard/426425}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
In the winter of 2017, Østigård signed a three-year contract with [[Molde FK]]. Ahead of the [[2018 in Norwegian football|2018 season]], he went on loan to [[Viking FK]] in [[Norwegian First Division|1. divisjon]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Leo Østigård har bestemt seg. I dag reiser han til Stavanger|url=https://www.aftenbladet.no/100Sport/fotball/Leo-Ostigard-har-bestemt-seg-I-dag-reiser-han-til-Stavanger-251831b.html|website=www.aftenbladet.no|publisher=[[Stavanger Aftenblad]]|accessdate=26 August 2018|language=Norwegian|date=12 March 2018}}</ref>

===Brighton & Hove Albion===
After the loan with Viking expired, Østigård signed for [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]].<ref name=brighton>{{cite web|title=ALBION SIGN NORWEGIAN YOUNGSTER|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/2018/august/albion-sign-norwegian-youngster/|website=www.brightonandhovealbion.com|publisher=[[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]]|accessdate=26 August 2017 |language=Norwegian|date=8 August 2018}}</ref>

====Loan to St. Pauli====
On 19 July 2019, [[FC St. Pauli]] signed Østigård on a loan deal until the end of 2019–20 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fcstpauli.com/news/fc-st-pauli-leiht-leo-ostigard-aus/|title= FC St. Pauli leiht Østigård aus|publisher=FC St. Pauli|language=German|date=19 July 2019|accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref> He made his debut for the [[Hamburg]] based club on 31 August coming on as a substitute in a 3–3 draw against [[Dynamo Dresden]].<ref>{{cite web|title=ST. PAULI PEGGED BACK AT DRESDEN|url=https://www.fcstpauli.com/en/news/published/dresden-match-report-a19-20/|accessdate=31 August 2019|date=31 August 2019}}</ref> He made his first start for St. Pauli which was against fierce rivals [[Hamburger SV]] where ''Kiezkicker'' won 2–0, claiming a first home win in 59 years against their local side.<ref>{{cite news|title=St Pauli beat Hamburg at home for first time in 59 years - BBC Sport|work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49727861|accessdate=17 September 2019|date=16 September 2019}}</ref>

====Loan to Coventry City====
On 27 August 2020, Østigård joined [[EFL Championship|Championship]] side [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] on a season-long loan deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ccfc.co.uk/news/2020/august/transfer-leo-ostigard-joins-coventry-city-on-loan-from-brighton/|title=TRANSFER: Leo Ostigard joins Coventry City on loan from Brighton|publisher=[[Coventry City F.C.]]|date=27 August 2020|accessdate=27 August 2020}}</ref> He made his debut on 12 September in which was his first senior game in English football where he played the full game in a 2–1 away defeat at [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bristol City 2–1 Coventry City: Tomas Kalas gives Holden's side victory - BBC Sport|work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54037694|accessdate=12 September 2020|date=19 October 2020}}</ref>
On 27 February 2021, Østigård was sent off in a 1–1 away draw at [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]] after picking up a second yellow card.<ref>{{cite news|title=Blackburn Rovers 1-1 Coventry City: Matty James equaliser cancels out Ben Brereton's opener - BBC Sport|work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56134781|accessdate=27 February 2021|date=27 February 2021}}</ref> Østigård scored his first goal in English football on 5 April opening the scoreline in an eventual 3–1 home victory over Bristol City.<ref>{{cite news|title=Coventry City 3-1 Bristol City: Sky Blues claim important win in survival bid- BBC Sport|work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56560220|accessdate=4 April 2021|date=4 April 2021}}</ref> Østigård returned to ''The Seagulls'' with two remaining games of the season due to a thigh injury. He made 39 appearances in the league scoring two goals – 40 apprarances, two goals overall – helping ''The Sky Blues'' to safety on their return to the Championship after eight years.<ref>{{cite web|title=Leo Ostigard says Coventry farewells and returns to Albion - BBC Sport|url=https://www.theargus.co.uk/sport/19273029.leo-ostigard-says-coventry-farewells-returns-albion/|accessdate=1 May 2021|date=1 May 2021}}</ref>

====Loan to Stoke City====
On 10 August 2021, Østigård joined [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] on loan for the [[2021–22 Stoke City F.C. season|2021–22 season]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Leo Ostigard: Stoke City sign Brighton & Hove Albion defender on season-long loan - BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58156839 |website=BBC Sport|date=10 August 2021|access-date=10 August 2021}}</ref> He made his debut that evening, playing the whole match of the 2–1 [[2021–22 EFL Cup|EFL Cup first round]] victory at home over [[EFL League One|League One]] side [[Fleetwood Town F.C.|Fleetwood Town]] in what was also his [[EFL Cup|League Cup]] debut.<ref>{{cite web |title=Stoke City 2-1 Fleetwood Town - BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58066027|website=BBC Sport |date=10 August 2021|access-date=11 August 2021}}</ref> Four days later he made his league debut for ''The Potters'' keeping a clean sheet in a 0–0 stalemate away at [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Birmingham City 0-0 Stoke City: Blues and Potters stay unbeaten after stalemate - BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58124644|website=BBC Sport |date=14 August 2021|access-date=14 August 2021}}</ref> On his third appearance he scored Stoke's third goal knocking in a rebound in a 3–1 away victory over [[Swansea City F.C.|Swansea City]] on 17 August.<ref>{{cite web|title=Swansea City 1-3 Stoke City: Sam Clucas goads Swans fans as Potters ease to victory - BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58154317|website=BBC Sport |date=17 August 2021|access-date=17 August 2021}}</ref> On 27 December 2021, Østigård was recalled from his loan spell by Brighton.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/3549069/2021/12/29/brighton-to-cut-short-leo-ostigards-loan-at-stoke-city/|title= Brighton to cut short Leo Ostigard's loan at Stoke City|publisher=The Athletic|date=27 December 2021|access-date=3 January 2022}}</ref>

====Loan to Genoa====
Østigård signed for [[Serie A]] side [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]] on loan for the [[2021–22 Genoa C.F.C. season|rest of the season]] on 5 January, after progressive previous loan spells and this signing giving him the chance to play at the top level.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/2440731/leo-ostigard-joins-genoa-on-loan|title=Leo Østigård joins Genoa on loan|publisher=Brighton & Hove Albion|date=5 January 2022|access-date=5 January 2022|archive-date=13 January 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250113074414/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/2440731/leo-ostigard-joins-genoa-on-loan|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his debut four days later, playing the whole match of the 1–0 home loss against [[Spezia Calcio|Spezia]] in the league, in what was his 100th club career appearance.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://genoacfc.it/event/genoa-vs-spezia/|title= Genoa vs Spezia - Genoa Cricket and Cricket and Football club - Official Website|publisher= Genoa Cricket and Cricket and Football club - Official Website|date=9 January 2022|access-date=9 January 2022}}</ref> 
In the week day away fixture against [[A.C. Milan|Milan]] in the [[2021-22 Coppa Italia#roundof16|Coppa Italia Round of 16]] on 13 January, Østigård scored his first ever domestic cup goal opening the scoring in the eventual 3–1 after extra-time loss.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.acmilan.com/it/news/articoli/coppa-italia/2022-01-13/qualificazione-ai-supplementari-il-milan-vola-ai-quarti|title= QUALIFICAZIONE AI SUPPLEMENTARI, IL MILAN VOLA AI QUARTI|publisher= A.C. Milan|date=13 January 2022|access-date=14 January 2022}}</ref> He came on as a substitute in the 0–0 away draw at [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] on 5 February, where he was shown a straight red card on the 68th minute.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.asroma.com/en/matches/e6c3be4af50b3d758f18ab9b/roma-vs-genoa#tab_match-stats=team-stats&tab_match-pitch=formation&tab_match=play-by-play|title= Roma 0-0 Genoa - Official AS Roma Website|publisher= Roma|date= 5 February 2022|access-date= 6 February 2022|archive-date= 18 October 2022|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20221018104048/https://www.asroma.com/en/matches/e6c3be4af50b3d758f18ab9b/roma-vs-genoa#tab_match-stats=team-stats&tab_match-pitch=formation&tab_match=play-by-play|url-status= dead}}</ref> Østigård was sent off for a second time in five matches, this time being shown two yellows after just 24 minutes of play in the 1–0 home victory over [[Torino F.C.|Torino]] on 18 March.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.nettavisen.no/sport/skiri-ostigard-sa-rodt-etter-bare-24-minutter-i-serie-a/s/12-95-3424257772|title= Football - Skiri Østigård saw red adter just 24 minutes in Serie A|publisher=nettavisen.no|date=18 March 2022|access-date=19 March 2022}}</ref>

===Napoli===
On 10 July 2022, Østigård transferred to [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]] in [[Serie A]] on a permanent transfer.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Napoli|url=https://sscnapoli.it/il-napoli-ufficializza-lacquisto-di-ostigard/|title=IL NAPOLI UFFICIALIZZA L'ACQUISTO DI OSTIGARD|date=18 July 2022|access-date=19 July 2022|language=it}}</ref> On 26 October 2022, he scored a goal on his [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut in a 3–0 win against [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2035705--napoli-vs-rangers/ |title=Napoli 3–0 Rangers |website=UEFA |date=26 October 2022 }}</ref>

===Rennes===
On 30 July 2024, Østigård transferred to [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] in [[Ligue 1]] for €7 million to stay until 2027.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Devaux |first=Grégoire |date=29 July 2024 |title=Rennes set to complete €7M deal for Naples' Leo Østigård |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2024/rennes-set-to-complete-e7m-deal-for-naples-leo-ostigard/ |access-date=2 September 2024 |website=GET Football}}</ref> He made his debut for Rennes on 18 August against [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] in a 3–0 win, playing all 90 minutes.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Entwistle |first=Luke |date=18 August 2024 |title=Rennes predicted XI v Lyon: New-look side set to kick off new Ligue 1 campaign |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2024/rennes-predicted-xi-v-lyon-new-look-side-set-to-kick-off-new-ligue-1-campaign/ |access-date=2 September 2024 |website=GET Football}}</ref> Against [[Stade de Reims|Reims]] on 1 September, Østigård recorded his first goal for Rennes in the 13th minute, assisted by [[Ludovic Blas]]. Rennes went on to lose the game 1–2.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Stade de Reims 2-1 Rennes: results, summary and goals |url=https://en.as.com/resultados/futbol/francia/2024_2025/directo/regular_a_3_481767/ |access-date=2 September 2024 |website=as.com}}</ref>

====Loan to Hoffenheim====
On 3 February 2025, Østigård was loaned by [[TSG Hoffenheim]] in Germany.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=TSG Hoffenheim|url=https://www.tsg-hoffenheim.de/en/news/overview/2025/02/tsg-sign-leo-ostigard-on-loan-from-stade-rennes|title=TSG sign Leo Østigård on loan from Stade Rennes|date=3 February 2025|access-date=4 February 2025}}</ref>

===Return to Genoa===
On 29 July 2025, Østigård returned to [[Genoa CFC|Genoa]] on loan with an option to buy and a conditional obligation to buy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Genoa CFC|url=https://genoacfc.it/2025/07/29/leo-skiri-ostigard-e-un-giocatore-del-genoa/|title=Leo Skiri Østigård è un giocatore del Genoa|trans-title=Leo Skiri Østigård is a Genoa player|date=29 July 2025|access-date=29 July 2025|language=it}}</ref> On 31 January 2026, Genoa made the transfer permanent.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Genoa CFC|url=https://genoacfc.it/2026/01/31/il-genoa-riscatta-in-anticipo-leo-skiri-ostigard/|title=Comunicato Ufficiale – Acquisto Leo Østigård dal Rennes|trans-title=Official Statement – Leo Østigård Acquired from Rennes|date=31 January 2026|access-date=31 January 2026|language=it}}</ref>

==International career==
After being capped at all youth levels he made his senior debut for the [[Norway national football team|Norwegian national team]] playing the whole match helping keep a clean sheet in a 2–0 friendly win at home over [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]] on 25 March 2022.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.fotball.no/landslag/norge-a-herrer/2022/disse-starter-mot-slovakia/|title= 2-0 win against Slovakia: A very deserved victory - Norwegian Football Association|publisher=fotball.no|date=25 March 2022|access-date=26 March 2022}}</ref> He scored his first senior international goal on his eighth appearance on 17 November, heading home from a [[Martin Ødegaard]] corner in the 2–1 friendly win away at the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63624354|title=Republic of Ireland 1-2 Norway: Visitors strike late to snatch friendly win|website=BBC Sport|date=17 November 2022|access-date=17 November 2022}}</ref>

